    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "RhKO9Rp-V0FE"
      },
      "source": [
        "stop_words = stopwords.words(\"english\")\n",
        "PONCTUATION = re.compile('[/(){}\\[\\]\\|@,;]')\n",
        "BAD_SYMBOLS = re.compile('[^0-9a-z #+_]')\n",
        "\n",
        "def text_prepare(text):\n",
        "    text =  text.lower()# lowercase text\n",
        "    text =  re.sub(PONCTUATION,\" \",text)\n",
        "    text =  re.sub(BAD_SYMBOLS,\"\",text)\n",
        "    text =  \" \".join([word for word in word_tokenize(text) if word not in stop_words])# delete stopwors from text\n",
        "    text = text.strip()\n",
        "    return text"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"

    },

        "sentiment_changer = {\"neutral\":0, \"negative\":1,\"positive\":2}\n",
        "y_train = y_train.map(sentiment_changer)\n",

        "y_train"

      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7Z3MUW_EeeN3"
      },
      "source": [
        "def tokenize_features(X_train, X_test):\n",
        "    tfidf_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(ngram_range=(1,2), max_df=0.9, min_df=5, token_pattern= '(\\S+)' ) \n",
        "    tfidf_vectorizer = tfidf_vectorizer.fit(X_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "    X_train_tfidf = tfidf_vectorizer.transform(X_train)\n",
        "    X_test_tfidf  = tfidf_vectorizer.transform(X_test)\n",
        "    vocab = tfidf_vectorizer.vocabulary_\n",
        "    return X_train_tfidf.todense(),  X_test_tfidf.todense(), vocab\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "FDSntQIN0tm6",
        "outputId": "8328dee2-5f6e-4bfc-88d5-8ee360779860"
      },
      "source": [
        "X_train_tfidf,  X_test_tfidf , vocab = tokenize_features(x_train,x_test)\n",
        "X_train_tfidf.shape"

      "source": [
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10,12))\n",
        "\n",
        "optimizer = 'adam'\n",
        "model = Sequential()\n",
        "model.add(Dense(units=512, activation='relu', input_dim=X_train_tfidf.shape[1]))\n",
        "model.add(Dropout(0.2))\n",
        "model.add(Dense(units=256, activation='relu'))\n",
        "model.add(Dropout(0.2))\n",
        "model.add(Dense(units=3, activation='softmax'))\n",
        "model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer=optimizer, metrics=['accuracy'])\n",
        "\n",
        "history = model.fit(X_train_tfidf, y_train, validation_data=(X_test_tfidf, y_test), epochs=100, verbose=0)\n",
        "\n",
        "print('Accuracy with',optimizer,'optimizer is :',model.evaluate(X_test_tfidf, y_test)[1]*100)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'], label='train')\n",
        "plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'], label='test')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.title('opt='+optimizer)\n",
        "plt.show()"

        "def get_key(val):\n",
        "    for key, value in sentiment_changer.items():\n",
        "         if val == value:\n",
        "             return key\n",
        "    return \"key doesn't exist\""

        "def classify(text):\n",
        "  tfidf_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(ngram_range=(1,2), max_df=0.9, min_df=5, token_pattern= '(\\S+)' ) \n",
        "  tfidf_vectorizer = tfidf_vectorizer.fit(x_train)\n",
        "  text_tfidf = tfidf_vectorizer.transform([text])\n",
        "\n",
        "  Xnew = text_tfidf.todense()\n",
        "  ynew = model.predict_classes(Xnew)\n",
        "  return (ynew)"

      },
      "source": [
        "Now as we saw, the accuracy of our model (72%) was quit good. Howeever, it is not as much as we wanted it to be.\n",
        "\n",
        "This could be due to two facts:\n",
        " * The model finds it hard to correctly classify the minority classes.\n",
        " * Not enough data to train on.\n",
        "In order to solve this kind of problems, we opted for the data augmentation techniques on our text data for the two minority classes. Later on we could see the evolution of our model performance."
      ]

        "Now we have a more balanced data"

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "_bt-OatV0tnC",
        "outputId": "6c5a0183-f503-43ec-a780-4d8edad057e6"
      },
      "source": [
        "x_train,x_test,y_train,y_test = train_test_split(aug_data.text,aug_data.sentiment,test_size = 0.2 , random_state = 0)\n",
        "\n",
        "sentiment_changer = {\"neutral\":0, \"negative\":1,\"positive\":2}\n",
        "y_train = y_train.map(sentiment_changer)\n",
        "y_test = y_test.map(sentiment_changer)\n",
        "\n",
        "encoder = OneHotEncoder()\n",
        "y_train = to_categorical(y_train)\n",
        "y_test = to_categorical(y_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "X_train_tfidf,  X_test_tfidf , vocab = tokenize_features(x_train,x_test)\n",
        "X_train_tfidf.shape\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10,12))\n",
        "\n",
        "optimizer = 'adam'\n",
        "model = Sequential()\n",
        "model.add(Dense(units=512, activation='relu', input_dim=X_train_tfidf.shape[1]))\n",
        "model.add(Dropout(0.2))\n",
        "model.add(Dense(units=256, activation='relu'))\n",
        "model.add(Dropout(0.2))\n",
        "model.add(Dense(units=3, activation='softmax'))\n",
        "model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer=optimizer, metrics=['accuracy'])\n",
        "\n",
        "history = model.fit(X_train_tfidf, y_train, validation_data=(X_test_tfidf, y_test), epochs=100, verbose=0)\n",
        "\n",
        "print('Accuracy with',optimizer,'optimizer is :',model.evaluate(X_test_tfidf, y_test)[1]*100)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.plot(history.history['accuracy'], label='train')\n",
        "plt.plot(history.history['val_accuracy'], label='test')\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.title('opt='+optimizer)\n",
        "plt.show()"
